# External Integrations

Any code that calls a 3rd party API (e.g., Stripe, SendGrid, Twilio, AWS) must be cleanly abstracted.

## Wrapper Service Pattern
- Never sprinkle direct API calls (e.g., `fetch()`, `axios.get()`) inside your core domain services.
- Create a dedicated wrapper service for the integration.
{{#if isNestJS}}
- Place the wrapper in `src/external/<service-name>/`.
- Provide the service via an explicit module (`StripeModule`) and export the service.
{{else}}
- Place the wrapper in `src/external/<service-name>.ts`.
- Instantiate the service with necessary API keys from config and inject it or import it where needed.
{{/if}}

## Error Handling
- Do not let 3rd party HTTP errors bubble up as raw HTTP responses to our clients.
- Catch all 3rd party SDK errors in the wrapper service.
- Map them to your own domain exceptions. Log the raw 3rd party error (with correlation IDs) internally.

## Retries & Timeouts
- Use an HTTP client that supports circuit breakers, timeouts, and automatic retries for transient errors.
- Do not hang indefinitely on external service calls. Set hard timeouts (e.g. 5000ms max).

## Webhooks
- Webhooks must verify cryptographic signatures provided by the 3rd party.
- Offload heavy processing from webhook endpoints to background queues immediately after verification.
